description:
&lt;p&gt;This a new development opportunity for a Community Staff Nurse to divide their time between the Complex Wound Clinic in Staines and the Community Nursing Team which covers the Spelthorne Locality in NWS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work alongside the Senior District Nurse in the wound care management of patients on the clinic caseload for up to 3 days a week and spend up to 2 days a week within the Community Nursing Team seeing patients in their own homes in the Spelthorne Locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally the post holder will be full time ,37.5 hours over a 7 day week but part time hours will be considered for the appropriate candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be part of the weekend rota which is usually once every 3-4 weeks, depending on annual leave. This is a fantastic learning opportunity for a candidate who loves community nursing but also wishes to start to specialise in wound care.&lt;/p&gt;
